-- Baht Steady After Central Bank Keeps Interest Rates Unchanged
-- B y   Y u m i   T e s o
-- 2012-05-02T07:29:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/baht-steady-after-central-bank-keeps-interest-rates-unchanged.html
Thailand ’s baht maintained today’s
decline after the central bank left borrowing costs unchanged at
a policy review today.  The baht fell 0.1 percent from its April 30 close to 30.78
per dollar as of 2:25 p.m. in Bangkok, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg. Local financial markets were closed
yesterday for a public holiday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yumi Teso in Bangkok at 
 yteso1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sandy Hendry at 
 shendry@bloomberg.net . 